Company Overview of Boyar Value Fund, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Boyar Value Fund, Inc. is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Boyar Asset Management, Inc. The fund is co-managed by Ladenburg Thalmann Fund Management, LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalization. The fund focuses on factors such as buy and hold investment strategy, company's balance sheet, companies whose shares are not widely held by institutions, or are not closely followed by investment analysts, or may have plummeted in value because they failed to meet analysts' earnings expectations, fundamen...
Boyar Value Fund, Inc. is an open ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Boyar Asset Management, Inc. The fund is co-managed by Ladenburg Thalmann Fund Management, LLC. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalization. The fund focuses on factors such as buy and hold investment strategy, company's balance sheet, companies whose shares are not widely held by institutions, or are not closely followed by investment analysts, or may have plummeted in value because they failed to meet analysts' earnings expectations, fundamental financial characteristics of a company, including debt-to-capital ratios, and the market capitalization to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P 500 Index. Boyar Value Fund, Inc. was formed on May 5, 1998 and is domiciled in the United States.
